                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">796.00/8–349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Philippines</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-04T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 4, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>928. Thus far ltr contained your 1889 Aug 3<note n="1" xml:id="d363fn1">See
                        footnote 1, <ref target="#pg_1182">p. 1182</ref>.</note> has recd little or
                    no publicity this country. Obviously story under Wash dateline wld carry
                    implication US had brought this ltr to pass. Very important ltr receive wide
                    publicity both here and Asia. Suggest you get in touch immed with Romulo so that
                    he can take steps on his own initiative to ensure wide publicity. No doubt he
                    will already have had ltr sent to all Phil missions with suggestions they give
                    it to govts to which accredited and to press in those countries. However,
                    important that stories in Amer press shd be recd from Manila and published under
                    Manila dateline.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
